  "title": "Solid and hollow yo-yo",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram consisting of two disks, labeled A and B. Disk A is solid and Disk B is hollow. A string is wrapped around each disk. The disks are placed side by side, where one end of each string is attached to the horizontal ceiling above. At the moment shown in the diagram, both disks are positioned at the same height.\" src=\"/images/20fde155c2b24cda0a00f69ac173ecd5.svg\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two disks have equal masses and radii. Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> is solid, and Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> is hollow. Each disk has a thin string wrapped around it. Both strings are attached to the ceiling as shown. The disks are simultaneously released from rest from the same height. Which of the following accurately describes which disk will hit the ground first and why?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> will hit the ground first. Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> has a greater rotational inertia; therefore, the tension in the string for Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> will be greater than the tension in the string for Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> will hit the ground first. Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> has a smaller rotational inertia; therefore, it will have a greater angular acceleration.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> will hit the ground first. Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> has a smaller rotational inertia; therefore, it will have a greater linear acceleration.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> will hit the ground first. Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> has a greater rotational inertia; therefore, it will have a greater angular acceleration.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Both disks will hit the ground at the same time. Since both disks have the same mass, they will have the same linear acceleration.</p>",
        "value": "i5"
      }
    ]
  },
